🛑 The Golden Grading Rule
Do not grade yourself until AFTER you type reboot. If a service fails to start on boot, or a mount point drops you into emergency mode, you score 0 points for that entire task. Partial credit is rarely given in the real world for a system that doesn't boot.

Task 0: The Gatekeeper
Points: 0 (Pass/Fail Dependency)

Grading: If you could not change the password and boot into the system, the exam is over.

Solution Overview:

Append rd.break to the kernel line in GRUB.

mount -o remount,rw /sysroot

chroot /sysroot

passwd root (set to sovereign2026)

touch /.autorelabel

exit and exit

Task 1: Network Configuration (10 Points)
Grading: 5 pts for correct IP/Hostname. 5 pts if it connects automatically on reboot.

Solution Overview:

Bash

hostnamectl set-hostname sovereign-node.example.com
nmcli con mod "eth0" ipv4.addresses 192.168.X.50/24 ipv4.method manual connection.autoconnect yes
nmcli con up "eth0"
Task 2: User and Group Administration (10 Points)
Grading: 2 pts for each user/group correctly created. 2 pts for Bob's password policy.

Solution Overview:

Bash

groupadd sysadmins
useradd alice && usermod -aG sysadmins alice
useradd -u 2050 bob && usermod -aG sysadmins bob
useradd -s /sbin/nologin charlie
chage -M 30 bob
Task 3: Collaborative Directories (10 Points)
Grading: 5 pts for group ownership. 5 pts for the SGID bit and removing "other" permissions.

Solution Overview:

Bash

mkdir -p /shared/ops
chgrp sysadmins /shared/ops
chmod g+s /shared/ops
chmod o-rwx /shared/ops  # (Or chmod 2770 /shared/ops)
Task 4: Advanced Permissions (ACLs) (5 Points)
Grading: 5 pts if getfacl /var/tmp/fstab_backup shows user:charlie:rw-.

Solution Overview:

Bash

cp /etc/fstab /var/tmp/fstab_backup
setfacl -m u:charlie:rw /var/tmp/fstab_backup
Task 5: Local Storage (LVM) (20 Points)
Grading: 5 pts for PV/VG creation. 5 pts for exact extent math (50 extents). 10 pts for persistent mounting without booting into emergency mode.

Solution Overview:

Bash

pvcreate /dev/vdb
vgcreate -s 16M vg_data /dev/vdb  # -s sets extent size
lvcreate -n lv_database -l 50 vg_data  # -l (lowercase) uses extent count
mkfs.xfs /dev/vg_data/lv_database
mkdir -p /mnt/database
blkid /dev/vg_data/lv_database  # Copy UUID
echo "UUID=<uuid> /mnt/database xfs defaults 0 0" >> /etc/fstab
mount -a
Task 6: Swap Space (10 Points)
Grading: 5 pts for creation. 5 pts for persistence in /etc/fstab.

Solution Overview:

Bash

fdisk /dev/vdc # (Create a 512M partition, e.g., /dev/vdc1)
mkswap /dev/vdc1
blkid /dev/vdc1 # Copy UUID
echo "UUID=<uuid> swap swap defaults 0 0" >> /etc/fstab
swapon -a
Task 7: System Maintenance & Automation (10 Points)
Grading: 10 pts if crontab -l -u alice shows the exact correct time format.

Solution Overview:

Bash

crontab -e -u alice
# Add this line:
23 14 * * * logger "Alice checking in"
Task 8: Archive and Search (5 Points)
Grading: 5 pts if /root/backup.tar.gz exists and contains the correct files.

Solution Overview:

Bash

mkdir /root/large_files
find /etc -size +5M -exec cp {} /root/large_files/ \;
tar -czvf /root/backup.tar.gz /root/large_files
Task 9: Security (SELinux and Firewalld) (10 Points)
Grading: 5 pts if Apache runs on 8282 (SELinux fix). 5 pts if accessible via curl (Firewall fix).

Solution Overview:

Bash

# Edit /etc/httpd/conf/httpd.conf and change "Listen 80" to "Listen 8282"
semanage port -a -t httpd_port_t -p tcp 8282
firewall-cmd --permanent --add-port=8282/tcp
firewall-cmd --reload
systemctl enable --now httpd
Task 10: Container Management (10 Points)
Grading: 5 pts for rootless deployment. 5 pts for systemd integration and lingering.

Solution Overview:

Bash

su - alice
podman pull nginx
podman run -d --name web_agent -p 8080:80 nginx

# Setup Systemd
mkdir -p ~/.config/systemd/user
podman generate systemd --new --name web_agent > ~/.config/systemd/user/container-web_agent.service
systemctl --user daemon-reload
systemctl --user enable --now container-web_agent.service

# Return to root to enable lingering
exit
loginctl enable-linger alice
